member.summary:
Handles a resource proxy request.
E.g. POST https://endpoint/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/{resourceProviderNamespace}/{resourceType}/{resourceName}/{proxySuffix}
The proxy suffix can contain multiple segments. The suffix includes all remaining segments in the URL after the last matching resource type and resource name.

Proxies the resource request. This call pattern is used for resource actions and nested proxy resources:
E.g. POST https://endpoint/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/{resourceProviderNamespace}/{resourceType}/{resourceName}/{proxySuffix}
The proxy suffix can contain multiple segments. The proxy suffix includes all remaining segments in the URL after the last matching resource type and resource name.
